  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ghana&#x2019;s Strengthened Accountability Mechanisms Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.Education and Awareness raising campaigns and capacity building 
Dissemination of performance and Financial score cards 
Radio and Information center discussions and playing of jingles in local language 
2. Stakeholders Engagement
Community Entry 
Preparation of Community Score Cards 
3.Application of ICT in monitoring DAs projects and Advocacy Campaigns 
Feed DAs Available information on Capital Development projects and Auditor General&#x2019;s annual Report finds on the E-Platform. 
Receive Messages from Citizens on malfeasance regarding Capital development projects.
4.Use of Behavior Change Communication 
Develop 10 BCC messaging on Selected local governance issues 
Print 9000 BCC Materials 
Distribute 9000 BCC materials to citizens and stakeholders

5.Formation of District Steering Committees
Formation of District Steering committee
Quarterly meeting of District Steering committee</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.Improved citizens and CSOs capacities to access available information to demand Accountability and transparency at the local level
2.Improved planning with regards to Annual Development Plans and public financial Management practices. 
3.Increased responsiveness to the public and the development and conduct of Annual Development plans 
4.Reduced corruption in capital development projects contracting process. 
5.Increased citizens engagement with the establishment of development planning priorities</narrative>
  </description>
